  "text": "It has been shown that basophil reactivity distinguish patients that tolerate extensively heated forms of cow's milk and egg from patients who do not. BAT may be useful in assessing the natural resolution of food allergies that are commonly outgrown over time, such as cow's milk allergy [CITATION_1] and in determining when the food can safely be reintroduced in the diet. BAT has also been used to monitor clinical response to immune-modulatory treatment of food allergy.",
